		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1957688&TN=proper+healing+technique&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1957688&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Clerics are one of the best and yes easiest classes to play and to also piss other people off. First thing to remember is to watch the agro at all times. In high agro situations you should try to use your HoT spells(Health Over Time, ie: Celestial Healing, etc) These heal alot of health is spurts and give very low agro. Second when u cast a heal make sure u call out to your group that u r healing and whom u are healing, so all the other healing classes know not to heal the same person, this saves alot of mana for all involved and lastly if for some reason you do get a angry mob on you for Pete's sake do not run like a sissy. Be calm stay still and let the tanks remove it from you. Remember we have the resurection spells so if we die who's gonna bring them back to life for free. EQ revolves around the healers anybody who tells u different does not know what they are talking about. I've seen groups pass on lvl 44 tanks to let a lvl 36 cleric in a grp in Karnors Castle a lvl 45 plus zone. We set the tone, but a bad cleric can ruining a great group. Thats my 2 cents do what u like with it. Peace  }:&gt<img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>Follower Of Innoruuk 42 lvl Cleric on Saryn server Orahn Khahn<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
