		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1957688&TN=proper+healing+technique&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2007164&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">This may be because I'm only a mid-level player yet, but personally I think that memming 4 healing spells is a bit of a waste of gems. If you mem 4 healing spells at a time you are reaching way back into the realm of spells that are no longer effective for your level. This is how I do my gems:</P><P>1- GHeal (awesome healing spell; a good 2 hp healed  for each mana used, fantastic ratio)<BR>2- Healing (good for casters that got too much aggro)<BR>3- Bravery (so that you can always have your buffs memmed for when they drop off of the tanks)<BR>4- Symbol of Ryltan (same as 3; I always ask for half compensation for the symbols, just so I'm not puring tons of money into keeping my group alive.)<BR>5- Smite (Just in case you are at FM and have nothing to do but make your bum sore and you want to hit something hard)<BR>6- Summon Drink (cause you never know when you need some water.)<BR>7- Summon Food (why do clerics always burn the bread? &lt;sigh>)<BR>8- Spirit Armor/Gate/Res spell/Root (cause any of these spells could come in handy and I have no reason not to mem them, especially cause people are always looking for a res)</P><P>I rarely use Celestial Remedy any more, because I can heal far mor HP with Gheal for less mana, and I can heal more HP with 3 heals with just about as good a ratio, even if it is slightly slower.</P><P>Please reply if you see the flaws in my philosophy. (And yes, I know I am behind in my spells; Kithicor scares me, eep...)</P><P>Nyena Elfinhealer<BR>High Elf Cleric of the 30th Orison<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
