		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=61&FN=Cleric&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1957688&TN=proper+healing+technique&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2007181&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1"><i>I rarely use Celestial Remedy any more, because I can heal far mor HP with Gheal for less mana, and I can heal more HP with 3 heals with just about as good a ratio, even if it is slightly slower.</i></P><P>Questhead, I think you might be missing the true value of the heal over time spells - they aren't about mana efficiency as such, their real use is in situations where you need to heal the tank without generating too much aggro. Could be just something to do with the places you're hunting though.</P><P>But for example, if you're in a situation where your groups puller might be coming back with 2 or 3 mobs at once, maybe he/she's pulling without SoW - e.g in a dungeon or something. Chances are the puller might show up with 2 or 3 mobs, and be low on health already by the time he/she reaches the group - you need to get a heal in quick. And if you hit the puller with a greater heal, then thats gonna pull 1 or 2 mobs straight onto you, as no-one else will have built up any aggro on em yet. A heal over time spell will avoid this and most likely save <i>your</i> life, never mind anyone elses.</P><P>Sure, it might be rare that you do need to use a heal over time, but I always have one memmed when I'm playing my cleric because they can definite lifesavers in certain situations.</P><P>But yeah, at lvl 30 I'd have 3 heals memmed - Healing, GHeal, and a heal over time.</P><P>(Oh, and root - I always, always, always have root memmed...)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
