		<hr size="1">I play a high lvl cleric and I have 4 heals and at least on Divine memmed. I do it a liitle different than most. And yes, unless its a dogfight, I melee.</P><P>1. DA<BR>2. Mark Of the Righteous<BR>3. Mark of Kings<BR>4. Yaulp or Root<BR>5. Ethereal Elixer (Group Heal over time)<BR>6. CH<BR>7. Supernal Remedy (fast heal)<BR>8. Supernal Elixer  </P><P>Trader makes a good point. If 2-3 are incomming and beating on the puller you HAVE to heal him. Just be ready to either root park or DA (at high lvls root parking isnt always an option) if you use a fast heal. </P><P>IF you ues a HoT u can let him build a bit of aggro before you use the fast heal or CH. Sometimes I will use the fast heat TO GET the adds on me and give the chanter/slower time to do thier thing on the adds (plate is your friend). </P><P>And then sometimes you just have to heal him for as much as you can, as fast as you can. Then it's DA or believe in your team.</P><P>Whatever you do, dont put yout HoTs away. You can use them after you CH to keep the tank up and it gives you time to fall back down on the hate list. Nothing worse than casting that heal and being summoned and buried.</P><P><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=236679>Venerable XYRO<br>Phantom Raiders of Bertoxxulous</a><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
